## Context

- crc-liquid-biopsy-panel: Completed panel architecture comparison and threshold impact assessment.
- Task 1291 (panel architecture): Three architectures compared. Protein-only (nested CV, n=121): AUC 0.871, sens@95spec 47.7%, $105. Methylation-only (LOO-CV, n=24): AUC 0.979, sens@95spec 83.3% — HIGH overfitting risk, CI [58.3%-100%]. Combined: AUC 0.900, sens@95spec 62.7% — worse than protein at 95% spec (operating point paradox).
- Task 1293 (threshold lowering): 69.5% sensitivity claim is training performance, not validated. Recomputed: 54.2% from predictions, 47.7% from nested CV. Protein panel identical at both thresholds. LASSO excludes methylation due to 15x cost overpenalty ($75/CpG vs correct $5/CpG).
- Created developer tasks: #1336 (fix LASSO cost weight), #1337 (bootstrap validation for methylation), #1338 (CpG-to-gene mapping).
- Created data_curator task: #1340 (find independent cfDNA methylation validation cohort n>=100).
- Created research_director task: #1339 (review >80% sensitivity finding with overfitting caveat).
- Key outputs: panel_architecture_comparison.json, threshold_impact_analysis.json in output/diagnostics/crc-liquid-biopsy-panel/.
- No pending analyst tasks remain. Next: wait for developer bootstrap validation (#1337) and corrected LASSO (#1336), then re-evaluate. Methylation validation cohort (#1340) is the critical blocker for advancing methylation architecture.
